In the United States, it is written in its Constitution that the protection of heritage is part of the culture of Americans and that this heritage must be protected by all citizens, all elected people and all government departments, and all of this, in concert.
In Quebec, in the Federation of Historical Societies of Quebec, at least 40,000 charitable people grouped into 211 societies of history, heritage, archives and genealogy are concerned with searching for history, preserving with little money lots of private archives, and preserving archaeological vestiges.
